section
  h2 Multiple cursors
  ul
    li <b>Ctrl + click</b> | <b>⌘ + click</b>
    li <b>Ctrl + double click</b> | <b>⌘ + double click</b>
    li <b>Ctrl + click, then shift + click</b> | <b>⌘ + click</b>
    li <b>Select block, then Shift + Ctrl + L</b> | <b>⌘ + Shift + L</b>

section
  h2 Editing
  ul
    li Select word: <b>Ctrl + D</b> | <b>⌘ + D</b>
    li Select all the word ocurrences: <b>Alt + F3</b> | <b>Ctrl + ⌘ + G</b>
    li Select line: <b>Ctrl + L</b> | <b>⌘ + L</b>
    li Indent line: <b>Ctrl + ], Tab</b> | <b>⌘ + ], Tab</b>
    li To uppercase: <b>Ctrl + KU</b> | <b>⌘ + KU</b>
    li To lowercase: <b>Ctrl + KL</b> | <b>⌘ + KL</b>


section
  h2 Code commands
  ul
    li Duplicate line: <br/><b>Shift + Ctrl + D</b> | <b>⌘ + Shift + D</b>
    li Code comment: <br/><b>Ctrl + /</b> | <b>⌘ + Shift + /</b>
    li Retrieve closed tab: <br/><b>Shift + Ctrl + T</b> | <b>⌘ + Shift + T</b>
    li Search incrementally: <br/><b>Ctrl + I</b> | <b>⌘ + I</b>
    li.fragment <a href="http://www.ractoon.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/sublime_text_2_shortcuts_printable_ractoon.pdf?11f46a" target="_blank">More shortcuts</a>

section
  h2 Snippets
  pre
    code.
      <snippet>
        &lt;content>&lt;![CDATA[
        Hello, ${1:this} is a ${2:snippet}.
        ]]>&lt;/content>
          &lt;!-- Optional: Set a tabTrigger to define how to trigger the snippet -->
          &lt;!-- &lt;tabTrigger>hello&lt;/tabTrigger> -->
          &lt;!-- Optional: Set a scope to limit where the snippet will trigger -->
          &lt;!-- &lt;scope>source.python&lt;/scope> -->
        &lt;/snippet>

